Author: celestinno
Content: papers please is a game about being a cog in an unfeeling system and having to make tough decisions in order to take care of yourself and your family. You can struggle to become a good person, but that will cost you. Vallhalla is somewhat similar in that you are also a cog in the system since the world of vallhalla is depicted as this cyberpunk dystopia where things are controlled by corporations, but it focuses more on the humanity of the individuals inside of said system and how they navigate it, rather than focusing on difficult moral decisions

Author: joseph_anderson_
Content:
Consenting adults can pretty much do what they want. I don't want to open up that discussion.

Dorothy is effectively an adult. She can consent.

But she also has the body intentionally designed to be underage and caters to people who find that attractive. And zero work or commentary is provided to bridge the gap between our reality and the game's where a very serious and uncomfortable problem has turned into a commodity. No discussions about the VERY awkward ethical grey area that technology has reached with this. Instead the game just jokes about her having so much sex and playing into the role as if it's all fun and no big deal.

Author: kaylio64
Content:
like as the xc1 fan, but xc2 hater let me say a nuanced take:

xc1 is rife with flaws that the series expanded upon and fixed and it clearly isn't better than the rest of the series in every single way ever, in fact multiple aspects are rather rough and could do a better job explaining cos once in a popup tutorial is unfortunately something people will insta skip over

xc2 suffers from having expectations from the series and the rather overly anime cartoon joke tone at the start is a bit overpowering and is not consistent throughout the game, it's not mixed in well and not retained throughout. discounting this, the xenoblade 2 plot does eventually get to a consistent tone and comes together, and there's quite a lot to appreciate though some people don't see it as often due to not being immersed and not taking it as seriously. I think the torna dlc does a lot to address this.

Author: _medley
Content: I'm watching blind, but I'm still on yesterday's stream. the game is interesting. I wasn't expecting such a slice of life kind of story, and I honestly dig it in some regards. I think some of the writing is pretty alright to good. There's some really good dialogue and characterization in some parts. It does have some stuff bringing it down. The sex stuff, while not all bad, is kinda tropey and just thrown in there pretty frequently without any actual point. It's not a super big deal, but it does contrast with the tone of the game a bit. I do like the tone and vibe of the game overall though, and the character designs are gorgeous.
